                        h2 Feedback management process:
                        p.lead
                            | Consider the following steps as you structure your feedback management process:
                        h2 Define objectives
                        p.lead
                            | Define your objectives by consulting with the product team, product ops team (if applicable), and other stakeholders for goal alignment.
                        h2 Feedback type
                        p.lead
                            | Specify the type of feedback sought, whether focused on user complaints, bug reports, or one-on-one interviews with key users. Always clearly define the type of feedback you prioritise.
                        h2 Preferred medium
                        p.lead
                            | Develop a systematic process for collecting market voices. Determine the methods for collecting feedback, choosing between forms, emails, feedback management system, or direct interviews.                            
                        h2 Organising feedback
                        p.lead
                            | Gather feedback and organise it into relevant categories. Establish an effective organisation system for the gathered feedback, avoiding the pitfalls of ignoring it. Utilise this gathered information to enhance your organisation's throughput.
                        h2 Action plan
                        p.lead
                            | Analyse the data to gain a comprehensive understanding of clients' perspectives and trends. Develop a plan for taking actionable steps based on the feedback, with a dedicated product ops team playing a strategic role. 
                        h2 Reconnect
                        p.lead
                            | Ensure feedback management includes reconnecting with customers who provided input for a comprehensive process. Enhance customer satisfaction by incorporating qualitative feedback, recognizing that customer success is a pivotal factor in your business's growth.

